HEADWORD: Cardialgy
<hw>Car"di*al`gy</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. <ets>cardialgia</ets>, fr.
Gr. <?/; <?/ heart + <?/ pain: cf. F. <ets>cardialgie</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A burning or gnawing pain, or feeling of
distress, referred to the region of the heart, accompanied with cardiac
palpitation; heartburn. It is usually a symptom of
indigestion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

